LOCATOR RECORD

Title: Physical Activity and Physical Fitness (PAQ)

Years of Content: 2010

First Published: April 2011

Last Revised: May 2013

Subject: Physical Activity

Record Source(s): Modified from NHANES

Data File: paq_2010.sas7bdat

Component Description

The Physical Activity and Physical Fitness (PAQ) section asks the respondent about physical activites that were done over the past 30 days. The first series of questions are related to transportation, then daily activity, followed by questions regarding physical activities during leisure time.

Eligible Sample

SHOW participants ages 21-74 are eligible for this section.

Interview Setting and Mode of Administration

The PAQ section was completed during the in-home (Time1) interview of a participant by a trained interviewer using computer-assisted personal interview (CAPI) form January 2010 to December 2010.

Data Processing

The PAQ section data were systematically reviewed for logical, processing, and data input errors during the process of data collection and entry by the University of Wisconsin Survey Center. Further data processing and cleaning were done by staff of the Survey of the Health of Wisconsin.

Analytic Notes

These data were collected as part of the in home personal interview portion of the SHOW study (Time 1), and T1 sample weights should be used when analyzing these data. Some participants provided impossible responses to some of the questions in the physical activies questionnaire. These impossible values were re-coded to “missing” values during data cleaning. If a participant reported doing an activity more than 24 hours each time, that response was re-coded to “missing”. Furthermore, there are other large values (reported by some participants) remaining in the dataset. While these values are not impossible, it is recommended that researchers review the data and decide how to handle these large values in their analysis.
